@{U}1.2.1  Hardware requirements                                  TeraDesk@{u}  
  
Tera Desktop  can  be  used on any Atari ST series  computer and their  
offspring, TT, Falcon, Hades, Milan or emulators. It uses about 200 to 
300 KB of memory (depending on the complexity of configuration). 

If a computer has TT-RAM or Alt-RAM installed,  it is  recognized  and 
used by Tera Desktop.

Although  Tera Desktop can be used without the aid of a hard disk, the  
use of one is strongly recommended.  On machines without  a hard disk, 
but with enough memory,  a reset-proof RAM-disk can be used to contain
TeraDesk files, which will speed statup considerably.  

It should be noted that Tera Desktop is not  well optimized for use on
machines with only one floppy drive and no hard disk.  File copying in 
TeraDesk is done file-by-file, which, when copying files from one disk
to another on a machine with only one drive,  will mean a lot of  disk 
swapping. 

Tera Desktop has not been tested with ROM-port cartridges which behave
as drive 'c' (lowercase C). It can be expected that such 'drive'  will 
not be recognized, or that other problems may occur.
  
@endnode  
  
