@{U}1.2.2 TOS Version compatibility                               TeraDesk@{u}  
  
Tera  Desktop should work with all existing versions of  TOS but it is  
very  much  more  useful  with  versions  1.04 (also known as 1.4) and  
above. There are several reasons for this, because in TOS version 1.04  
and above:  
  
- Folders can be renamed.  
  
- The  file processing routines are  very much  better and enable more  
facilities to be used.  
  
- GEM  programs   (including  Tera  Desktop  itself)  can  be  started  
automatically after booting.  
  
- There are significant bugs in TOS 1.0 and TOS 1.02 (1.2)  
  
- Functionality  of  Tera Desktop is reduced  with  TOS versions older  
than 1.04 (1.4) because of limitations on the size of menus.  
  
Since Version 2  TeraDesk  runs in modern  multitasking  environments,  
such as  MagiC,  TOS with Geneva,  Mint with N.Aes,  XaAES,  MyAES  or 
Atari AES 4.1.  It can run with  memory protection;  however,  in such
environments  problems  may  occur  with  some  incorrectly-programmed
or set AV-protocol clients  which can cause  TeraDesk to crash  if run 
with memory protection. See The AV protocol. 
  
TeraDesk 3* was tested on a number of system configuration, including:  
  
TOS 1.00 (RAM-loaded)  
  
TOS 1.02 + Mint 1.15.12 + AES 4.1 / N.Aes 2.0 / XaAES 0.970  
  
TOS 1.04  
TOS 1.04 (RAM-loaded)  
TOS 1.04 + NVDI 2.0   
TOS 1.04 + Mint 1.15.12 + AES 4.1 / N.Aes 2.0 / XaAES 0.970  
  
TOS 2.06  
TOS 2.06 + NVDI 4.11  
TOS 2.06 + NVDI 4.11 + Wdialog 2  
TOS 2.06 + NVDI 4.11 + AES 4.1
TOS 2.06 + NVDI 4.11 + MyAES 2.1
TOS 2.06 + Geneva 4 / 6 + NVDI 4.11  
TOS 2.06 + Mint 1.15.0  + NVDI 4.11 + AES 4.1 / N.Aes 1.1 / XaAES 0.970 
 
TOS 2.06 + Mint 1.15.12 + AES 4.1 / N.Aes 2.0 / XaAES 0.970  

TOS 3.05 + NVDI 2.0   
TOS 3.06  
 
Hades TOS 3.06 + oVDI 
Hades TOS 3.06 + Mint 1.16 + oVDI + N.Aes 2.0 / XaAES

TOS 4.04  
TOS 4.04 + Mint 1.15.12 + AES 4.1 / N.Aes 2.0 / XaAES 0.970  
  
Milan TOS 4.09 + MiNT 1.15.12 + N.Aes 1.2 / XaAES  
  
KAOS TOS  
  
MagiC 6.0 + NVDI 5.0   
MagiC 6.1 + NVDI 4.11  
MagiC 6.2 + NVDI 4.11  
  
The program is  supposed to work  (with some restrictions) on TOS 1.0,
bat the last versions of TeraDesk much  tested with it. Possibility of 
encountering  hitherto  undetected problems with this  TOS version  is 
suspected.

A  problem  was  encountered  related  to  mouse clicks on the desktop  
icons  when  TeraDesk  was  running in TOS 2.06 (only). An attempt was  
made  to  cure  this,  but  it  is  not  sure  yet whether it has been  
completely successful. Similar problem may exist in TOS 3.06. 
  
Change  of  screen  resolution works with various success in different  
AESses  (generally  supported with AES 4 versions only), e.g. in TOS +  
Geneva  or  TOS  +  Mint  +  AES4.1  it works perfectly; in some other  
environments it doesn't work so well, or not at all.  

TeraDesk  makes  several  inquires  trying  to determine TOS- and AES-  
versions  and  their  capabilities and limitations. If some version of  
TOS  or  AES  is  not  able to answer these queries, TeraDesk tries to  
make guesses  which  may  not  always be correct.  It is also possible  
that  incorrect  answer to an inquiry is supplied by TOS/AES, in which  
case TeraDesk  may  work  with unnecessary limitations  or else try to  
activate features which may not work. 

If TeraDesk is used with the new AESses currently being developed (e.g
XaAES or MyAES,  occasional unwanted behaviour  may occur  because  of
some features of these AESes  which are not yet fully functional. Such
issues usually get resolved with new releases of the AESses.

If TeraDesk is used on an emulator,  some of its  functionality may be
lost because of sometimes incomplete emulation. Such cases may include
e.g not  recognizing certain keyboard key codes,  or not being able to 
show  directories in 'unsorted' order.
 
See also Screen resolutions  
  
