@{U}4.2.10 Format disk...                                         TeraDesk@{u}  
  
When this item is selected  and a floppy drive icon  is also selected,  
the dialog of the Floppy format function appears on the screen.  
  
The dialog offers many options:  
  
4 densities:  
     Single sided    (SSDD)  
     Double sided    (DSDD)  
     High density    (DSHD)  
     Extra density   (DSED)  
  
For each density chosen, further parameters  can  be specified,  which
will modify the basic format  (editable  only  after  selectig a basic
format):  
  
    number of sides  
    number of tracks  
    number of sectors per tracks  
    directory size  
    volume label  
      
If  this  operation  is  used  in a multitasking environment  (Mint or 
Magic),  an  attempt  is  made  to lock the floppy drive device before 
commencing formatting.  If it fails  (e.g. if the device is already in
use), formatting can not be commenced.
      
Note  that  this item might not be present in the copy of TeraDesk you 
are  using,  i.e.  it is possible to compile Tera Desktop without this 
function.  

Formatting operation can be interrupted by pressing the [Esc] key.

See also Screen resolutions 
  
@endnode  
  
@node "Quit/Shutdown"  
@toc "Menu title: File"  
