@{U}4.2.11 Quit/Shutdown                                          TeraDesk@{u}  
  
Select this item to quit Tera Desktop and either:  
1: return to the standard desktop   
2: return to the AES fallback desktop (e.g. Geneva, N.Aes,  AES 4.1 or 
   XaAES)  
3: shut down the computer completely  
   
If option 3 is selected in a multitasking environment  the appropriate 
shutdown procedure is activated. 
   
Note  that  only  a  very  simple  sequence of  shutdown operations is 
performed:  shutdown is invoked by shel_write(...) function, which may 
not  have  any  effect in older versions of the AES. After shel_write, 
and  after  waiting for several seconds, if TeraDesk is still alive, a 
Shutdown() is initiated (in restart mode), but only if Mint is present. 
If TeraDesk is still alive after -that-, a brute-force reset is done. 
   
If a  more  sophisticated  shutdown  is required, an external Shutdown 
utility should be used. 
   
See also Set applications...
     
@endnode  
  
  
