When this option is ticked, files and folders in directory windows are
shown as icons. When the option is not ticked, they are shown as text. 
  
In  text mode,  item size in bytes, the creation date and time and the 
file attributes can be shown as well as the file name. 
  
Which  of  the  above  are  shown is determined by the Show options in 
this menu. 

Note:  in earlier versions of TeraDesk  there were two menu items  for
controlling  the appearance  of  directory windows: 'Show as text' and
'Show as icons'. As one of them was in fact redundant,  'Show as text'
was removed in order to minimize complications created by limited menu
size in old versions of TOS (see TOS Version compatibility).
  
@endnode  
  

@node "Auto arrange"  
@toc "Menu title: View"  
@image udo_fo.img 1  
   Contents  
@image udo_fo.img 4  
      Menus and Dialogs  
@image udo_fo.img 7  
         Menu title: View  
  
@{U}4.3.2  Auto arrange                                           TeraDesk@{u}  
  
When this option  is selected,  TeraDesk will  attempt to optimize the 
use of screen area when displaying directory windows. This means that:

- In text mode (see Show as icons) the directories may be displayed in 
  one or several  columns,  depending on  screen width  and the length
  of directory lines,  which, in turn, depends on selection of visible 
  fields  (see  Show options...).  This options  is  especially usable
  when it is needed  to display as many items in a directory window as
  possible.  Choice of a smaller font for directory windows  increases
  the number of columns that can be displayed on the screen. 
  
- In icon mode the directories are displayed with icons rearranged  to
  fit the current  widths  of  the windows.  Horizontal  scrolling  of
  the windows is not possible, nor needed.
  
When this options is deselected:

- In text mode directories are displayed in one column only.

- In icon mode the  directories are displayed  with icons  arranged to 
  fit the whole width of the screen.  Horizontal slider can be used to 
  scroll  the window to  left or right  in order to make  some  of the
  items visible.
  
A note: it can be  expected that  manipulation of windows  (scrolling,
changing size,  etc.)  will  be  somewhat  slower  when  display is in 
the  text mode  and  this option is selected.  On the  contrary,  when
display is in icon mode,  window manipulation may be slower  when this
option is -not- selected.
    
@endnode  


  
@node "Sort by..."  
@toc "Menu title: View"  
@image udo_fo.img 1  
