@{U}4.3.3  Sort by...                                             TeraDesk@{u}  
  
With these items you can select the order in which the files displayed   
in a window are sorted. The possibilities are:  
  
               1.   Sort by name  
               2.   Sort by extension  
               3.   Sort by creation date  
               4.   Sort by size  
               5.   View unsorted  
  
Items  are sorted in the ascending order. Note that, in 'Sort by size' 
and 'Sort by date' modes it is contrary to the TOS desktop which lists 
first the largest and newest files. See also Reverse order.
  
If  you  select  'View unsorted',  items are displayed in the order in 
which  they were stored on the disk; note that this is not necessarily 
the  same as  the order of  their creation,  but  depends also  on the 
history of additions and deletions in the particular directory. 
  
The mode selected applies to all open windows.  

If you  are  running TeraDesk in low or medium  screen resolution  and
TOS 1.0, 'View unsorted'  menu item may not be visible, because of the 
limitations in this TOS version. 

See also: TOS Version compatibility  Screen resolutions
  
@endnode 


