@{U}4.3.4  Reverse order                                          TeraDesk@{u}  
  
Normally,  items in directory windows of  TeraDesk  are sorted  in the 
ascending order,  with all subfolders of the displayed directory being
displayed first. If 'Reverse order' option  is checked  this behaviour
will be reversed.  This also applies to subfolders which will be shown
at the end of the list of visible items.
    
The mode selected applies to all open windows.  

If you  are  running TeraDesk in low or medium  screen resolution  and
TOS 1.0, 'Reverse order'  menu item may not be visible, because of the 
limitations in this TOS version. 

See also: Sort by... TOS Version compatibility  Screen resolutions
  
@endnode 

  
