@{U}4.3.5  Show options                                           TeraDesk@{u}  
  
With  these  items  you  can  select  the  amount of information shown 
alongside  the object name when in text mode. The selected options are 
ticked.  
 
               1.   Show size  
               2.   Show date  
               3.   Show time  
               4.   Show attributes  
  
Selection applies to all open directory windows.  
  
The attributes which are set are denoted as follows:  
  
               d        directory  
               -        permission not granted or attribute not set.  
  
For TOS file system(s):  
               s        system file  
               h        hidden file  
               w        writable file (opposite of write protected)  
               a        archive bit  
  
For VFAT or UNIX file systems:  
  
              l         link  
                
        repeated for user, group and world:  
  
              r        read permission  
              w        write permission  
              x        execute permission  
  
(In some file systems the last three attributes are 'faked').

If you  are  running TeraDesk in low or medium  screen resolution  and
TOS 1.0,  these  menu  items   may not  be  visible,  because  of  the 
limitations in this TOS version. 

See also: TOS Version compatibility  Screen resolutions

@endnode  
  
  
