@{U}4.4.1  Close                                                  TeraDesk@{u}  
  
If  you  select  this item, the current (top) window is closed. If the 
window  is  the  directory  window  of a folder, it is replaced by the 
window  of  the  directory which is one level higher. If the window is 
the  directory  window of a disk volume root, the window is closed. If 
the window is a text (viewer) window, it is closed. 

If an application has  signed-on itself as an  AV-protocol client, its
windows  can be included in the TeraDesk's  list of windows;  in  such 
cases, the 'Close' command applies to the client's windows as well.

See also Close window, Supported Protocols
  
@endnode  
  

  
