@{U}4.6 Keyboard shortcuts                                        TeraDesk@{u}  
  
Beside  being  selected  by  a  mouse,  menu  items  can  be set to be 
selected  by  pressing  a  key  or  a  key combination. These keyboard 
shortcuts are set in the Desk preferences... dialog. 
  
Likewise,  most  buttons  in  dialog boxes  can also be  selected by a 
key:  Press  and  hold  down [Alternate] and then press the key of the 
character in the button that is underlined. 
  
Boxes  with  arrows  can  be  selected  by  holding down [Control] and 
pressing the corresponding cursor (arrow) key on the keyboard. 
  
Directory  windows  on  disk  volume root directories can be opened by 
pressing  the  [Alternate][?]  key  combination  ('?' representing the 
drive   letter,   i.e.   A   to   P   or   A   to   Z).  Pressing  the 
[Alternate][Shift][?]  combination will open the root directory of the 
specified disk volume in the existing top window. 
  
If  [Shift][Help] key combination is pressed, TeraDesk will attempt to 
call ST-Guide,  if it is installed as an accessory  or already running
in any other way,  to  open  TERADESK.HYP  file  containing  this user 
manual. Another help program may be specified- see Configuration files

Pressing  [Help]  key  invokes a Help dialog  with brief  explanations 
of basic keyboard commands. 
  
@endnode  


  
@node "The listbox dialog"  
@image udo_fo.img 1  
   Contents  
@image udo_fo.img 4  
