@{U}4.8 The program type dialog                                   TeraDesk@{u}  
  
Here  you can specify the behaviour of the application when started in 
any way other than double clicking: 
  
The mode determines whether the specified command line is invoked.  
  
There are 5 modes:  
  
      GEM       AES/VDI application  
      GTP       Gem Takes Parameters  
      ACC       Accessory
      TOS       TOS program (no GEM) 
      TTP       TOS Takes Parameters; Unix style commandline programs  
  
See also Types of program files  
  
The current directory mode can also be set:  
  
Each  program  that  makes  use  of  ancillary files, like resource or 
configuration  files,  must  be able to find these files in a specific 
directory. This mode defines where this directory can be obtained. 
  
    Program          directory from which the program is started  
    Window           the directory of the top window of TeraDesk  
  
Compliance of the program with the ARGV protocol can be set:                                        TeraDesk@{u}  
  
The  number  of  characters which specify the parameters is limited to 
125  in  the standard desktop but Tera Desktop allows you up to employ 
more.  It  does  this by using The ARGV protocol. You should note that 
some  GTP  or  TTP  programs do not support the ARGV protocol; you can 
toggle its use on and off by clicking on the box. 
  
