@{U}4.11 The copy info dialog                                     TeraDesk@{u}  
  
If  a selection is made in the  Copy and print... options dialog  that 
some  file  operations  should  be  confirmed,  Copy info dialog  will 
appear. 
  
It  shows  the  numbers of folders and files on which the operation is 
to  be  performed,  the  initial  source path and, if appropriate, the 
destination path. 
  
For copy, touch and move/rename  operations, two checkbox buttons  are 
shown in the dialog:  
  
- Change date and time  
- Reset attributes  
  
If  'Change date and time'   is  set,  all files acted upon  will have 
their date and time stamp  changed to current values  (or, in the case 
of 'touch' operation, to values specified in Info... dialog). 
  
If  'Reset attributes' is set, attributes (read-only, system, etc.) of 
all files acted upon will be reset to normal values   (or, in the case 
of 'touch' operation, to values specified in Info... dialog).

For print operations,  three radio-buttons and a checkbox will appear,
permitting the user to set some printing options; see Print...

